WEBVTT

00:00:00.600 --> 00:00:09.991
Well, good morning family. It's late night, almost early morning, but I thought I'd pray with you all for a little bit.

00:00:09.992 --> 00:00:18.159
We went to the Branson prayer conference and what a time we had.

00:00:18.160 --> 00:00:24.630
It was wonderful. How's my audio? Tell us in the comment section down below how the audio is.

00:00:24.631 --> 00:00:31.096
We're trying a new mic because it echoes a lot, so we're trying to make it so you can hear us better.

00:00:31.097 --> 00:00:36.032
Let us know; if it's bad, we can switch back. I can push one button and it'll go back to the old one.

00:00:36.033 --> 00:00:44.289
If you don't like it, let us know. But we went to the prayer conference in Branson and it was wonderful.

00:00:44.290 --> 00:00:52.954
I really enjoyed that with Sister Billie and the family and Lynn and so many other people.

00:00:52.955 --> 00:00:58.016
They came from all over the place and it was awesome to see everybody.

00:00:58.017 --> 00:01:13.399
At the tent meeting we prayed; it wasn't live, televised, or livestreamed. There were demonstrations and manifestations.

00:01:13.400 --> 00:01:30.039
Pastor Tracy Harris from Texarkana came and laid hands on everyone in the whole tent revival and the power of God was knocking people down. It was amazing to see people get so blessed.

00:01:30.040 --> 00:01:44.936
Then they had the fish fry, but I got to speak at that tent meeting and that was the first time I've ever spoken to that many people for that long.

00:01:44.938 --> 00:02:05.180
Usually I talk a little bit and I've done that several times, but this is the first time anyone has really handed me the mic and said 'go with it.'So it was a real blessing to be able to pray and do the things that the Lord allowed me to do during that service.

00:02:05.181 --> 00:02:09.787
I believe it went pretty well. How can you judge your own thing?

00:02:09.788 --> 00:02:17.154
I just go by what they all said, and they said it was good. So I'm thankful for it.

00:02:17.155 --> 00:02:50.479
But now we're home and I have an urgency in my spirit to pray for our economy, to keep praying against delays, coming against what I believe is the enemy trying to rear his head, trying to stop the blessing of what the Lord is wanting for this body.

00:02:50.480 --> 00:03:06.999
As I was driving around today, coming back into town and doing the things that the Lord wanted us to do, He said to me, 'Brandon, you're going to have to contend for what I've told you to do.

00:03:07.000 --> 00:03:21.513
Don't just lay down and say, "whatever will be, will be."'Like that song, 'Whatever will be, will be, Que sera, sera.'It's not like that.

00:03:21.514 --> 00:03:35.334
We have got to take our authority and we have got to start praying over what God has told us to do and not just sit there and say, 'Well, whatever will be, will be.'He said, 'Brandon, you're going to have to contend for it.

00:03:35.335 --> 00:03:48.519
You're going to have to fight for it, lay hold to it.'He said, 'Whenever I told the children of Israel to go and get the land, they had a choice.

00:03:48.520 --> 00:04:05.959
They could either say God is with us and who can be against us or have the attitude of a winner mentality, or you can shrink back and go, "well, we're the size of grasshoppers."'The first generation did that and they died in the wilderness.

00:04:05.960 --> 00:04:12.239
But God had to raise up a whole new generation of people to go and take the land for Him.

00:04:12.240 --> 00:04:20.798
And that's the kind of people that have the bulldog mentality that go after it like a dog on a bone and say, 'You know what?

00:04:20.799 --> 00:04:46.519
I'm fighting and contending for what's mine.'And the Lord told me, 'For what I've called you to do, everything that I have, it's not a victim mentality that gets you there.

00:04:46.520 --> 00:04:53.865
You have a victor mentality, a winner mentality, but a winner mentality contends.

00:04:53.866 --> 00:05:00.199
They fight for it; they say, "This is mine."'Do you understand what I'm saying?

00:05:00.200 --> 00:05:16.426
It has to be that: how bad do you want it in these end times with all the stuff that's going on around us. There's so much every single day, ladies and gentlemen.

00:05:16.427 --> 00:05:24.021
I just go, 'My goodness, this has been incredible.'Even look at what we stopped, I believe, with the Atlanta shooting.

00:05:24.022 --> 00:05:35.260
The guy went in saying he wanted to do something at the airport, had 27 shots and a firearm.

00:05:35.261 --> 00:05:48.392
He walked into the airport, but his family told on him and he was brought to justice by the police department there.

00:05:48.393 --> 00:05:54.084
Thank God that's an answer to prayer. That right there shows we're contending. We're fighting.

00:05:54.085 --> 00:06:08.571
We're saying, 'No, you're not going to do this to our airports.'Because bottom line, ladies and gentlemen, we wrestle not against flesh and blood; we're wrestling against principalities and powers and spiritual wickedness in high places.

00:06:08.572 --> 00:06:25.686
This was a principality working through a personality. But I believe as we are praying believers that come in agreement and intercede for our nation, we're stopping this stuff.

00:06:25.687 --> 00:06:36.848
Now, I believe there's a lot more to stop. But praying for our economy to turn around—there are so many people saying we're in a recession.

00:06:36.849 --> 00:06:45.455
There are so many people saying that it's worse than 2008, that it's going to get worse than that and go into the Great Depression.

00:06:45.456 --> 00:07:00.359
And I said, 'Not yet.'So that's why I wanted you to come on here and pray with me tonight to pray over our economy so that we have that window.

00:07:00.360 --> 00:07:18.995
Now, I know I've heard other people say they believe a great economic crisis worse than 2008 will come in the next year, but I believe in God for a supernatural wealth transfer for the body of Christ before all this starts to take place.

00:07:18.996 --> 00:07:33.799
I told you I saw President Trump treading the river. It was like Niagara Falls, and he was paddling as fast as he could because the boat was going to go over.

00:07:33.800 --> 00:07:48.279
But he was keeping the economy from going clear over by paddling in that canoe as fast as he could because he knew that it was just a matter of time and it was going over.

00:07:48.280 --> 00:07:52.642
It's going into the beast system. That's where all this is headed.

00:07:52.643 --> 00:08:00.660
We all know that a one-world government, a one-world financial system is coming because that's what the Bible says.

00:08:00.661 --> 00:08:06.479
And so if that's coming, we're not going to stop it. Can we delay it and give us more time? Yes.

00:08:06.480 --> 00:08:12.214
I believe with our prayers and as we intercede, we're the salt and the light of this world.

00:08:12.215 --> 00:08:19.019
I believe that God has given us the ability to change a lot of things through prayer—delaying things, doing things.

00:08:19.020 --> 00:08:26.507
But I'm going to tell you, we're running out of time. Jesus Christ is coming.

00:08:26.507 --> 00:08:33.869
Now, I heard another man this week say, 'We're so far away from all that.

00:08:33.870 --> 00:08:57.868
Don't worry, Jesus isn't coming right now.'I don't doubt that we have a lot to do, but I'm going to tell you this: the time clock is ticking and we are at the midnight hour. I'm telling you, it's time to wake up.

00:08:57.869 --> 00:09:12.950
And that's why I've tried to warn you over and over, even at the prayer conference, trying to warn the people that a major shaking is about to take place in this earth to awaken it.

00:09:12.951 --> 00:09:26.499
It's not just about America. President Trump said today, 'Well, we have over 17 trillion dollars worth of stuff coming in.'I don't know where he's getting his numbers, but I pray that's true.

00:09:26.500 --> 00:09:37.119
I want an economic boom. I told you I saw the wave and it was transparent.

00:09:37.120 --> 00:09:44.879
You could see crypto, gold, silver, and the housing market through this.

00:09:44.880 --> 00:09:54.999
That means it was shallow. It wasn't a deep, defined wave, but it was a wave.

00:09:55.000 --> 00:10:02.959
Nevertheless, that's the word I would use. On top of the soil was gold. Do you all remember that?

00:10:02.960 --> 00:10:16.119
And the Lord said, 'There's enough gold on the layer of what's coming right here.'It was thin—not a thick foundation, but a thin one. He said, 'Enough to line your pockets, son.

00:10:16.120 --> 00:10:30.119
Fill your pockets as quickly as you can for what's about to come because it's not thick, it's thin.'And that wave will not last very long.

00:10:30.120 --> 00:10:44.039
It's a short-lived wave, but it will provide enough for an end-time wealth transfer for you to get the job done to bring in the harvest.

00:10:44.040 --> 00:10:51.279
It's not going to be long-lived, but it will give you enough time and enough money to get the job done.

00:10:51.280 --> 00:11:07.919
Jesus Christ is coming, and I'm telling you, brush arbor Churches, Woodstock Church—it's like Woodstock, Holy Ghost Woodstock. All this is coming; it's right at our door.

00:11:07.920 --> 00:11:22.317
But I've tried to tell some of the people, I said, 'We've got to have the money to get it done.'It costs millions and millions, if not hundreds of millions and tens of millions of dollars to get the gospel out.

00:11:22.317 --> 00:11:28.254
It's not free: TV time, radio time, all those kinds of things.

00:11:28.255 --> 00:11:42.879
The only thing that is free is these YouTubes; they've provided a platform for us to use that we can broadcast like this, and we get thousands of people watching on here, and it doesn't cost anyone anything.

00:11:42.880 --> 00:11:48.319
They just click on their internet provider and watch us on their phone or their tablet.

00:11:48.320 --> 00:11:55.146
Most people watch from their tablet or from their television, and some on phones.

00:11:55.147 --> 00:12:05.450
Which is it most, Braden? Phone and TV. I think it's pretty cool. And that's not TV time.

00:12:05.451 --> 00:12:11.959
We're using their platform, but they can turn us off anytime they want to. It's their platform. That's the part that's shaky.

00:12:11.960 --> 00:12:18.159
The moment we say something against what they believe or what they think, you're done.

00:12:18.160 --> 00:12:23.319
But I believe that persecution is not here yet to the point of where I believe it's coming.

00:12:23.320 --> 00:12:30.959
I told you it would be like an olive press in the days ahead, and the oil will come forth.

00:12:30.960 --> 00:12:40.079
Great persecution is coming on the church. And the Lord told me, 'The great harvest will come out of birthing pains.

00:12:40.080 --> 00:12:47.779
It will come out of a time of trials because people are not awake. People are not alert.

00:12:47.780 --> 00:13:07.064
They're not looking for the coming of the Lord Jesus Christ.'Many people are just like, 'I've heard it so much I don't believe it anymore, really.'There's a remnant of us who do, and those are the ones I believe are coming on here praying every single time we start prayer, and you're excited about it.

00:13:07.065 --> 00:13:17.076
Hey, this is a cool book: In Him by Kenneth E. Hagin. It's a little short read; it's 32 pages.

00:13:17.077 --> 00:13:23.359
I bet it's less than a dollar. You probably can get it for like 25 or 50 cents, I don't know, whatever.

00:13:23.360 --> 00:13:29.399
But it's a good read: In Him by Kenneth E. Hagin. Little short book, 32 pages.

00:13:29.400 --> 00:13:35.879
Pretty cool, huh? I like stuff like that; it's like a little pocketbook. Diana found that for me.

00:13:35.880 --> 00:13:43.310
I told her, 'Thanks, baby.'She got that and said, 'Hey, Brandon, I think you need to read this: In Him.'I have some more over there.

00:13:43.311 --> 00:13:51.522
Braden, will you get those other two little books mama got me over there?

00:13:51.523 --> 00:13:55.439
If Diana was here, she could read this to you in less than five minutes.

00:13:55.440 --> 00:14:06.105
She's a fast reader. Oh, she got me this one: The Precious Blood of Jesus by Kenneth E.

00:14:06.106 --> 00:14:12.055
Hagin. And then she got me The Gifts of Prophecy by Kenneth E.

00:14:12.056 --> 00:14:23.746
Hagin. And then she got me Praying to Get Results by Kenneth Hagin. They're all short reads.

00:14:23.747 --> 00:14:28.559
She gets me things that don't overwhelm me because I don't like to read that much anyway.

00:14:28.560 --> 00:14:35.519
But it has 71 pages in that one. So, it's a pretty cool little book she got me.

00:14:35.520 --> 00:14:42.530
It came in the mail; she got it from Amazon, I guess. She surprised me and said, 'Hey, I got that for you tonight.

00:14:42.531 --> 00:14:47.759
Look what I got you, Braden—Brandon.'So I'll share with Brent, my son.

00:14:47.760 --> 00:14:52.687
He can read one, and I'll read one a day. It keeps you stirred up.

00:14:52.688 --> 00:15:13.479
You have to fan that flame. You cannot let your flame go down in these last days.

00:15:13.480 --> 00:15:19.812
You have to stir yourself up. And that's what I'm trying to tell you. This is how I do it. This is how Diana does it.

00:15:19.813 --> 00:15:28.799
She'll read one of these little books, she'll drive around and say, 'Let's read that,'finding things to keep yourself stirred up in these last days.

00:15:28.800 --> 00:15:33.033
Don't wait on your pastor to feed you. Don't wait on the evangelist to feed you.

00:15:33.034 --> 00:15:36.159
Don't wait on a prophet to feed you. Don't wait on YouTube to feed you.

00:15:36.160 --> 00:15:43.258
You have to be a scavenger. How badly do you want your life to change?

00:15:43.259 --> 00:15:48.279
How desperate are you to find stuff? That's why we're always looking for stuff.

00:15:48.280 --> 00:15:55.435
My goodness, if I waited on my pastors to feed me only, you would die spiritually.

00:15:55.436 --> 00:16:02.320
Do you understand? You can't wait on people. You have to be a contender.

00:16:02.321 --> 00:16:20.119
The Lord said, 'Brandon, I'm putting my closers in.'He said, 'I've saved the best for last—my closers.'Diana and I started doing research on the closers; they are built for pressure.

00:16:20.120 --> 00:16:26.137
Closers in baseball—the ones that close the baseball game—are built for pressure.

00:16:26.138 --> 00:16:41.498
They don't lose the lead because they're not going, 'Oh gosh.'You know about buck fever when you're hunters and you're out there and your hands are shaking from the pressure of the buck walking in front of you.

00:16:41.499 --> 00:16:50.282
You miss the shot because you've got buck fever. That's where we are in these end times.

00:16:50.283 --> 00:16:56.440
God made us for pressure. He said, 'Brandon, we've got this, but you've got to be a contender.

00:16:56.441 --> 00:17:03.225
You can't just sit there and lay down on the job and say, "Stop."'Nobody feels sorry for you.

00:17:03.226 --> 00:17:08.639
That's what the Lord said. Nobody feels sorry for you. Do you understand?

00:17:08.640 --> 00:17:12.811
You've got to play the world's smallest violin for yourself?

00:17:12.812 --> 00:17:18.078
'You had a hard day. The enemy was attacking.'Stand up and fight.

00:17:18.079 --> 00:17:24.127
Be a contender. Say, 'No, I'm not going to let you do this. I'm not going to let you rob my family of finances.

00:17:24.128 --> 00:17:34.094
I'm not going to let you rob me of health. I'm not going to sit here and have a snotty nose and have all this going on with me.

00:17:34.095 --> 00:17:40.613
I refuse to do this. I have a covenant with God.'You either are or you aren't.

00:17:40.614 --> 00:17:49.719
Are you a believing believer or not? Are we believing believers in these last days or are we not?

00:17:49.720 --> 00:18:00.230
That's why I started saying, 'I'm done with this.'When you say you're barely getting by, or you're done not feeling good...

00:18:00.231 --> 00:18:13.119
'Oh, you're overweight.'Well, you eat too much. I work on myself daily.

00:18:13.120 --> 00:18:18.439
'Well, you feel sorry for yourself.'No, you're the one that put the food in there.

00:18:18.440 --> 00:18:26.766
You've got one hole; you don't have to keep putting food in it all day long.

00:18:26.767 --> 00:18:33.609
The Lord gets on me about a lot of stuff. I walk a very tightrope with the Father.

00:18:33.610 --> 00:18:52.119
He's instructed me on what I'm supposed to be doing with my life, telling me, 'This is how you get there.'He always said, 'Brandon, if you want change in your life, you're going to have to change the way you're doing things because you can't keep doing the same thing expecting different results.

00:18:52.120 --> 00:19:02.695
How badly do you want to go on with me? How badly do you want this?'You want impartation from these generals? You want impartation, but are you a contender for it?

00:19:02.696 --> 00:19:16.832
Do you do what they did to get it—from Billy Burke to Lynne Hammond to whoever you know has been in ministry for 50 or 60 years?

00:19:16.833 --> 00:19:24.597
Do you do what they did to get where they are? They've sustained it and they've been there.

00:19:24.598 --> 00:19:36.519
Or do you just sit there and go, "Well, you know, there's a reason why there's not very many of them."Nobody said it would be easy, but how bad do you want it?

00:19:36.520 --> 00:19:39.799
And that's why I thought about it. You know, there's only one Bill Gates.

00:19:39.800 --> 00:19:45.449
There's only one Warren Buffett. There's only one Elon Musk.

00:19:45.450 --> 00:19:50.285
I'm just talking about the wealthiest of the wealthiest. But they did something.

00:19:50.286 --> 00:19:58.559
And I'm not saying they did righteous things to get there, but I'm talking about people who contend for the greater wealth.

00:19:58.560 --> 00:20:05.079
It's a pattern. They have a different mindset. They think differently.

00:20:05.080 --> 00:20:12.399
They don't think poverty. They don't think quit. They don't think loser. They think winner.

00:20:12.400 --> 00:20:19.839
It's like when they say you could retire and never have to work again, "Elon, you're worth $500 million.

00:20:19.840 --> 00:20:26.826
You're the richest person in the world. Why do you keep working?"I was thinking, why?

00:20:26.827 --> 00:20:32.076
Why would you? You're never going to spend all that if you just had it by yourself.

00:20:32.077 --> 00:20:41.039
That's an absurd amount of money. He's almost halfway to a trillion dollars.

00:20:41.040 --> 00:20:51.331
Do you realize that's a lot money? That's rich. But yet you just have that drive to keep going.

00:20:51.332 --> 00:21:03.203
You're just built differently. What does it take to be in ministry for 50 years like my friends?

00:21:03.204 --> 00:21:08.837
Not a victim. Not somebody who's always whining about their life and about demonic attacks.

00:21:08.838 --> 00:21:16.519
That's why I checked myself. You're not a victim, Brandon. A victim's not going to make it.

00:21:16.520 --> 00:21:20.828
Whiners, don't be a whiner. Be a winner. That's what he said, Brandon.

00:21:20.829 --> 00:21:34.359
You're not going to do this and be a whiner. You're built for pressure. I said you were closers. I'm putting in my closers.

00:21:34.360 --> 00:21:40.159
So, every single one of you that are watching right now, I believe that God has called you for such a time as this.

00:21:40.160 --> 00:21:50.839
And he didn't build you to fail. He did not build you to be a whiner, but a winner.

00:21:50.840 --> 00:21:56.079
How bad do you want it in your life? I want change. And that's what I thought.

00:21:56.080 --> 00:22:15.597
All the times whenever it came down to working for minimum wage, working for barely getting by, and you work your tail end off by the sweat of your brow all day long for those eight hours a day, Monday through Friday, and you go get another job.

00:22:15.598 --> 00:22:20.408
You've got two jobs, you're working it, and you never make it.

00:22:20.409 --> 00:22:27.039
I've always read these books and I listen and I study about these people who have been successful.

00:22:27.040 --> 00:22:41.678
They have an idea to solve a problem. It's the problem solvers. It's creative. It's never the grunts.

00:22:41.679 --> 00:22:49.999
Well, I worked for this guy and I flipped burgers for him and I filled soda—I was a soda jerk or whatever.

00:22:50.000 --> 00:22:57.599
I worked at the convenience store. But it's always solving a problem.

00:22:57.600 --> 00:23:04.199
It's thinking outside of the box for ministry. How do we get more people saved?

00:23:04.200 --> 00:23:11.439
That runs through my mind all the time. How do we get more people saved for the kingdom of God?

00:23:11.440 --> 00:23:19.159
What we're doing is not working, is it? You get a hundred people saved. Is that working?

00:23:19.160 --> 00:23:38.559
When there's 8 billion plus that are dying and going to hell, is a hundred effective? The numbers aren't good enough. It needs to be millions.

00:23:38.560 --> 00:23:59.119
When there's eight billion, we need millions at a time, tens of millions to even be effective at all to be able to say, "Hey, you did something."But when you get a hundred, I'm so grateful for the hundred, but I'm trying to think bigger.

00:23:59.120 --> 00:24:09.199
How do I get there? How do you do that? I don't see anybody around me, even in my circle, that is even getting—I even say, "Do you even get an altar call?

00:24:09.200 --> 00:24:18.888
How many people did you get saved in the last year?"It is less than probably a thousand and they've been in ministry for 50 years.

00:24:18.889 --> 00:24:26.999
How many people did you get born again this year? Well, you know we got 500, 5,000.

00:24:27.000 --> 00:24:38.919
That's a fail. I don't care. You can't brag about that. I can't brag about that.

00:24:38.920 --> 00:24:47.225
There's 8 billion people going to hell and they're dying by the tens of thousands every couple of minutes.

00:24:47.226 --> 00:24:52.771
I don't even know the statistics of it. The mathematical equation of it is too big for my mind to comprehend.

00:24:52.772 --> 00:24:57.896
How many are being born? How many are dying? But how many of those people went to hell?

00:24:57.897 --> 00:25:16.430
Hell is enlarging its gates every second. People are dying. And I don't want to get excited and relax at a hundred souls.

00:25:16.431 --> 00:25:28.279
I'm thankful, but I see too many people slipping through the fingers. And I thought, how do you become more effective?

00:25:28.280 --> 00:25:34.919
And the only thing I can ever relate it to is what drew me: the anointing.

00:25:34.920 --> 00:25:39.159
It's the anointing. It's the anointing that breaks the yoke.

00:25:39.160 --> 00:25:59.039
Approximately 150,000 to 173,000 die a day. Did you show them that?

00:25:59.040 --> 00:26:06.474
I don't know how many other people—like I said, I don't see even in some churches that we don't even have altar calls that often.

00:26:06.475 --> 00:26:12.919
Maybe we get one a month, or if that, because there's no new converts coming.

00:26:12.920 --> 00:26:25.119
And if that's the case, that's what the Lord told me. He said there has to be a great—so I'm saying all that to say this today.

00:26:25.120 --> 00:26:40.885
The reason why I know—I don't just believe, I'm fully persuaded in what God has told me is coming: a great shaking to awaken, to draw the people up, to draw the people in.

00:26:40.886 --> 00:26:56.959
Yes, there's a great falling away. But the Lord said to me, "Brandon, I'm leaving the 99 and going after the one."But there will be a 24-hour period where everything will change.

00:26:56.960 --> 00:27:04.199
A great shaking to awaken is coming. Now, people ask, "When?"I don't know.

00:27:04.200 --> 00:27:09.584
But he told me as of the 23rd of September, this was the point of no return.

00:27:09.585 --> 00:27:20.580
And a great acceleration would begin at the 23rd involving the fig tree, the nations, the sheep and the goat nations.

00:27:20.581 --> 00:27:26.799
You would see a dividing line. Just like what happened—they took a vote at the UN.

00:27:26.800 --> 00:27:32.129
There were only three nations that stood by the state of Israel.

00:27:32.130 --> 00:27:39.779
The rest of the world turned their back and said no. They even walked out on Benjamin and his whole speech.

00:27:39.780 --> 00:27:49.088
So it's all about the fig tree. Do I stand with everything that Israel stands for?

00:27:49.089 --> 00:27:56.559
I always stand with Israel, but I don't always have to agree with some of the government decisions.

00:27:56.560 --> 00:28:04.039
It's like America. I pray for America and I live here, but I don't always agree with America's decisions.

00:28:04.040 --> 00:28:11.479
